1
00:00:45,520 --> 00:00:46,079
Stop staring.

2
00:00:46,159 --> 00:00:47,039
Move along, move along.

3
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:51,640
Captain Ma.

4
00:00:52,640 --> 00:00:53,520
Should we call the police?

5
00:00:56,000 --> 00:00:57,079
Are you stupid?

6
00:00:58,240 --> 00:00:59,159
We're the military.

7
00:00:59,399 --> 00:01:00,280
Why call the police?

8
00:01:01,560 --> 00:01:02,679
If word of this gets out,

9
00:01:03,560 --> 00:01:04,719
we'll be the laughingstock.

10
00:01:05,680 --> 00:01:06,920
If the Brigade Commander finds out,

11
00:01:07,159 --> 00:01:08,359
he'll have me shot.

12
00:01:09,599 --> 00:01:10,120
Then what about...

13
00:01:11,439 --> 00:01:11,640
This...

14
00:01:12,120 --> 00:01:13,040
those bodies in here?

15
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:16,640
You go

16
00:01:16,959 --> 00:01:18,159
find some reliable brothers,

17
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:20,159
bury them on the back hill at midnight.

18
00:01:21,640 --> 00:01:21,959
Go on.

19
00:01:22,719 --> 00:01:23,159
Yes, sir.

20
00:01:25,920 --> 00:01:26,239
Wait.

21
00:01:28,920 --> 00:01:29,319
Remember,

22
00:01:30,799 --> 00:01:31,959
find ones who can keep their mouths shut.

23
00:01:34,239 --> 00:01:34,760
Yes, sir.

24
00:01:44,719 --> 00:01:45,200
Alright.

25
00:01:45,239 --> 00:01:45,760
That's enough.

26
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:01,799
This money

27
00:02:02,079 --> 00:02:03,159
is from the Captain.

28
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:05,359
Keep your mouths shut.

29
00:02:06,120 --> 00:02:06,680
Yes, sir.

30
00:02:10,319 --> 00:02:10,800
Alright.

31
00:02:11,319 --> 00:02:12,159
You all head out first.

32
00:02:15,439 --> 00:02:16,159
Aren't we leaving?

33
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:18,080
I think this whole thing

34
00:02:18,319 --> 00:02:19,240
seems a bit fishy.

35
00:02:19,960 --> 00:02:20,719
I think so too.

36
00:02:21,240 --> 00:02:22,319
This was definitely done by a person.

37
00:02:24,080 --> 00:02:24,840
But who could it be?

38
00:02:35,759 --> 00:02:37,360
If only Master were here.

39
00:02:37,639 --> 00:02:38,400
He'd know for sure.

40
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:40,120
You miss your Master.

41
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:43,199
Master has flaws

42
00:02:43,199 --> 00:02:44,360
as numerous as the stars.

43
00:02:44,879 --> 00:02:45,479
His virtues

44
00:02:45,639 --> 00:02:46,560
are as scarce as the sun.

45
00:02:47,759 --> 00:02:49,439
But whenever the sun rises,

46
00:02:49,840 --> 00:02:50,759
all the stars

47
00:02:51,199 --> 00:02:52,199
fade into nothing.

48
00:02:54,240 --> 00:02:54,960
What kind of person

49
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:55,719
is your Master, really?

50
00:02:56,199 --> 00:02:56,879
Want to hear about him?

51
00:02:57,719 --> 00:02:58,280
Yes.

52
00:03:00,479 --> 00:03:01,919
I remember when I was sixteen...

53
00:03:17,719 --> 00:03:18,680
Where'd you get that gun?

54
00:03:19,840 --> 00:03:20,439
It's mine.

55
00:03:20,479 --> 00:03:21,039
Give it to me.

56
00:03:21,280 --> 00:03:21,840
Hand it over.

57
00:03:22,039 --> 00:03:22,759
Give it to me!

58
00:03:26,960 --> 00:03:28,039
It's a fake.

59
00:03:28,439 --> 00:03:29,360
What're you so nervous about?

60
00:03:30,400 --> 00:03:30,919
Listen to me,

61
00:03:30,919 --> 00:03:31,879
you can't carry even a fake gun.

62
00:03:31,879 --> 00:03:32,479
You hear me?

63
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:33,520
I'll carry it anyway.

64
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:34,879
And I'll get a real gun too,

65
00:03:34,879 --> 00:03:35,759
to kill the man who killed my mother.

66
00:03:36,080 --> 00:03:36,439
Brother.

67
00:03:36,639 --> 00:03:37,599
Why are you bringing this up again?

68
00:03:37,719 --> 00:03:38,800
Master said never to mention it.

69
00:03:39,000 --> 00:03:39,840
Why shouldn't I?

70
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:41,360
It wasn't your mother who died.

71
00:03:46,639 --> 00:03:47,800
It's "for my own good" again, huh?

72
00:03:48,840 --> 00:03:49,960
Don't you glare at me!

73
00:03:51,199 --> 00:03:52,080
Get down on your knees!

74
00:03:54,240 --> 00:03:54,560
Auntie Xiaoling.

75
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:54,960
Kneel down!

76
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:56,840
Didn't I tell you?

77
00:03:57,479 --> 00:03:58,319
Didn't I tell you?

78
00:03:58,319 --> 00:03:59,479
Never bring this up, ever.

79
00:04:01,479 --> 00:04:02,680
What are you two doing?

80
00:04:03,840 --> 00:04:05,599
Fighting and shouting over this little thing.

81
00:04:05,599 --> 00:04:06,400
Don't practice anymore.

82
00:04:06,800 --> 00:04:08,280
I train to build my strength,

83
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,400
you know?

84
00:04:09,479 --> 00:04:10,159
Look how skinny he is.

85
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:11,759
He couldn't even haul manure now.

86
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:13,319
You Lao Jiugui.

87
00:04:13,319 --> 00:04:14,159
Had too much to drink again?

88
00:04:14,520 --> 00:04:15,280
We're eating now.

89
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:16,160
Manure this, manure that.

90
00:04:16,399 --> 00:04:17,040
Come eat.

91
00:04:17,639 --> 00:04:18,639
It's all your favorites.

92
00:04:25,319 --> 00:04:25,920
Auntie Xiaoling.

93
00:04:26,120 --> 00:04:26,920
I'll go grab you a bowl.

94
00:04:27,399 --> 00:04:27,879
Such a good boy.

95
00:04:29,399 --> 00:04:30,279
Get up, Dongsheng.

96
00:04:31,519 --> 00:04:32,720
Go fetch some wine for your Master.

97
00:04:44,199 --> 00:04:45,240
I'll discipline the kid from now on.

98
00:04:45,240 --> 00:04:46,519
Could you stop interrupting?

99
00:04:47,079 --> 00:04:48,680
I'm afraid I'll hurt you by accident.

100
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:50,639
The kid's all grown up now.

101
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:51,920
You think it's like before?

102
00:04:59,439 --> 00:05:01,160
Get five doses with this prescription.

103
00:05:01,319 --> 00:05:02,240
Then the illness will be cured.

104
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:03,040
No need.

105
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:03,959
Just have...

106
00:05:04,480 --> 00:05:05,399
the doctor take a look.

107
00:05:06,560 --> 00:05:07,439
No need to pay.

108
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:07,839
No need.

109
00:05:08,639 --> 00:05:09,279
We don't...

110
00:05:09,519 --> 00:05:10,800
We have no money for medicine.

111
00:05:14,399 --> 00:05:15,000
Um...

112
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:16,360
Ruling!

113
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:17,399
Coming!

114
00:05:17,959 --> 00:05:18,680
Come here, come here.

115
00:05:20,680 --> 00:05:21,560
It's all right, it's all right.

116
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:23,480
That, um...

117
00:05:24,319 --> 00:05:26,319
Uncle Li needs to buy medicine.

118
00:05:26,800 --> 00:05:27,560
He's got no money.

119
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:28,560
Here, look.

120
00:05:29,319 --> 00:05:30,360
This should be enough.

121
00:05:30,920 --> 00:05:31,720
It's enough, it's enough.

122
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:32,600
This is plenty.

123
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:34,240
Thank you, Lao Jiugui.

124
00:05:34,279 --> 00:05:35,199
Thank you, Lao Jiugui.

125
00:05:35,439 --> 00:05:36,560
Get up, get up, get up.

126
00:05:37,839 --> 00:05:38,879
Take the money and get the medicine.

127
00:05:39,560 --> 00:05:40,480
Take the money and get the medicine.

128
00:05:41,160 --> 00:05:42,120
It's fine, it's fine.

129
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,319
All right, all right.

130
00:05:50,319 --> 00:05:51,240
Dao ke dao...

131
00:05:51,399 --> 00:05:51,759
Dao...

132
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:52,600
Dao ke...

133
00:05:53,639 --> 00:05:54,639
Dao what Dao?

134
00:05:54,720 --> 00:05:55,839
You're holding the book upside down.

135
00:06:09,279 --> 00:06:10,560
What are you looking at me for?

136
00:06:11,319 --> 00:06:12,560
Got peanuts on my face?

137
00:06:12,959 --> 00:06:14,279
Even with all the peanuts in the world,

138
00:06:14,279 --> 00:06:15,399
they're useless.

139
00:06:15,800 --> 00:06:17,480
Listen, listen, listen.

140
00:06:17,920 --> 00:06:18,319
It's empty.

141
00:06:18,319 --> 00:06:19,639
If it's empty, then stop drinking.

142
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:21,399
At your age,

143
00:06:22,800 --> 00:06:23,600
have some water.

144
00:06:23,759 --> 00:06:24,120
You...

145
00:06:28,480 --> 00:06:29,120
Water?

146
00:06:29,480 --> 00:06:29,680
This...

147
00:06:30,560 --> 00:06:31,079
Water...

148
00:06:31,360 --> 00:06:32,839
has no alcohol in it!

149
00:06:35,199 --> 00:06:36,079
My savior,

150
00:06:36,519 --> 00:06:36,920
um...

151
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:38,199
Have a heart,

152
00:06:38,319 --> 00:06:40,000
go fetch me some wine, won't you?

153
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:41,560
Just for tonight.

154
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:42,240
Okay?

155
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:43,879
Please?

156
00:06:43,879 --> 00:06:44,920
It's not that I won't go.

157
00:06:45,839 --> 00:06:46,480
This temple...

158
00:06:47,040 --> 00:06:48,160
really has no money left.

159
00:06:51,199 --> 00:06:52,160
Don't try to fool this old man.

160
00:06:52,800 --> 00:06:53,800
You think I don't know?

161
00:06:53,920 --> 00:06:55,399
The Mayor gives us...

162
00:06:55,639 --> 00:06:57,199
ten silver dollars every month.

163
00:06:57,639 --> 00:06:59,079
The Mayor gives that to you?

164
00:06:59,079 --> 00:07:00,240
Yes, it's given to me.

165
00:07:00,680 --> 00:07:01,439
He only gives it...

166
00:07:01,439 --> 00:07:03,240
out of respect for Marshal Sun.

167
00:07:03,839 --> 00:07:04,839
Even so,

168
00:07:05,000 --> 00:07:05,759
it's given to me.

169
00:07:06,360 --> 00:07:07,759
Marshal Sun was killed two years ago...

170
00:07:07,759 --> 00:07:08,800
by his Adjutant.

171
00:07:09,480 --> 00:07:11,000
The ten silver dollars stopped long ago.

172
00:07:15,879 --> 00:07:18,079
My ill-fated Marshal Sun!

173
00:07:21,279 --> 00:07:22,680
And the last silver dollar...

174
00:07:23,639 --> 00:07:25,000
you just gave away too.

175
00:07:27,759 --> 00:07:28,240
No way.

176
00:07:29,959 --> 00:07:31,000
I'm going to take it back.

177
00:07:31,079 --> 00:07:31,560
Go.

178
00:07:32,040 --> 00:07:32,680
Go quickly.

179
00:07:33,399 --> 00:07:33,800
Go on.

180
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:46,319
This...

181
00:07:47,959 --> 00:07:48,720
Then how have we...

182
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:50,000
gotten by these past two years?

183
00:07:52,319 --> 00:07:53,040
These two years,

184
00:07:53,079 --> 00:07:53,720
it's all been Auntie Xiaoling

185
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:54,959
earning it through mending clothes.

186
00:08:00,439 --> 00:08:01,279
That's been hard on you.

187
00:08:01,279 --> 00:08:01,920
Ruling.

188
00:08:03,160 --> 00:08:03,680
This hard...

189
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:19,920
What are you doing?

190
00:08:20,360 --> 00:08:21,120
There are kids around!

191
00:08:21,120 --> 00:08:22,759
You really ruin the mood.

192
00:08:23,160 --> 00:08:24,480
No wonder Master doesn't like you.

193
00:08:26,439 --> 00:08:27,480
Lao Jiugui!

194
00:08:28,160 --> 00:08:28,480
Coming!

195
00:08:28,480 --> 00:08:29,600
Lao Jiugui!

196
00:08:30,839 --> 00:08:31,920
Lao Jiugui!

197
00:08:34,279 --> 00:08:36,279
I'm begging you, please save me!

198
00:08:36,600 --> 00:08:37,440
What are you doing?

199
00:08:42,919 --> 00:08:43,600
You're kneeling to the wrong one.

200
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:45,039
Lao Jiugui!

201
00:08:45,879 --> 00:08:46,759
Lao Jiugui!

202
00:08:47,240 --> 00:08:47,919
Lao Jiugui!

203
00:08:48,360 --> 00:08:49,039
Save me!

204
00:08:49,039 --> 00:08:50,519
I beg you, please save my life!

205
00:08:50,559 --> 00:08:50,960
Lao Jiugui!

206
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:52,159
Aren't you from Hanging Gourd Hall,

207
00:08:52,159 --> 00:08:52,840
Shopkeeper Li?

208
00:08:53,159 --> 00:08:54,279
Who died in your family?

209
00:08:55,039 --> 00:08:55,720
Bring them over.

210
00:08:56,759 --> 00:08:57,360
Lao Jiugui!

211
00:08:57,759 --> 00:08:58,919
Nobody's dead yet!

212
00:08:59,000 --> 00:09:00,159
Lao Jiugui, at a time like this,

213
00:09:00,159 --> 00:09:01,879
could you stop joking around?

214
00:09:02,080 --> 00:09:03,360
I'm not joking either.

215
00:09:03,480 --> 00:09:04,120
Get up, get up.

216
00:09:04,120 --> 00:09:05,360
Take it slow.

217
00:09:05,600 --> 00:09:06,120
What's going on?

218
00:09:07,360 --> 00:09:07,960
Lao Jiugui,

219
00:09:09,120 --> 00:09:09,879
please come to my place

220
00:09:09,879 --> 00:09:10,919
and take a look.

221
00:09:11,919 --> 00:09:12,639
My house

222
00:09:14,279 --> 00:09:15,360
is haunted!

223
00:09:17,519 --> 00:09:18,159
Well, well...

224
00:09:18,799 --> 00:09:20,879
For ghosts, you need a Taoist priest.

225
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:22,840
I'm a Lamp Keeper.

226
00:09:22,840 --> 00:09:24,000
I can't catch ghosts.

227
00:09:24,879 --> 00:09:25,440
This is...

228
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:26,679
I really...

229
00:09:26,960 --> 00:09:27,799
There's nothing I can do.

230
00:09:29,240 --> 00:09:29,759
Well...

231
00:09:29,919 --> 00:09:30,360
I understand.

232
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:31,399
I understand.

233
00:09:31,399 --> 00:09:32,480
Lao Jiugui, look,

234
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:34,320
I get it.

235
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:37,559
Lao Jiugui,

236
00:09:38,039 --> 00:09:38,879
as long as you

237
00:09:38,879 --> 00:09:39,919
fix this for me,

238
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:41,120
afterwards,

239
00:09:42,039 --> 00:09:43,320
I'll show my appreciation.

240
00:09:43,759 --> 00:09:44,519
I'll also give you...

241
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,080
But I really...

242
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:46,840
Master,

243
00:09:47,519 --> 00:09:48,759
just agree to help him.

244
00:09:49,480 --> 00:09:50,519
I've never seen a ghost before.

245
00:09:50,759 --> 00:09:51,320
I want to go see one.

246
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:51,960
See what?

247
00:09:51,960 --> 00:09:52,759
Just read your books.

248
00:09:53,000 --> 00:09:53,840
You look like a ghost to me.

249
00:09:56,080 --> 00:09:57,279
Master,

250
00:09:57,480 --> 00:09:58,559
just agree to help him.

251
00:09:58,919 --> 00:09:59,759
You don't want Auntie Xiaoling

252
00:09:59,759 --> 00:10:00,519
to work so hard, do you?

253
00:10:03,039 --> 00:10:04,000
Well...

254
00:10:04,720 --> 00:10:06,120
I guess it's not impossible.

255
00:10:08,759 --> 00:10:09,320
Shopkeeper Li,

256
00:10:09,320 --> 00:10:10,919
do you have wine at home?

257
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:11,720
Yes!

258
00:10:12,360 --> 00:10:13,840
I have premium Tiger Bone Wine.

259
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:15,320
The finest quality.

260
00:10:15,360 --> 00:10:15,799
Right.

261
00:10:15,840 --> 00:10:16,120
Tiger bone—

262
00:10:17,279 --> 00:10:18,279
that's so nourishing.

263
00:10:19,200 --> 00:10:20,519
For you, it's not just a tonic.

264
00:10:20,639 --> 00:10:21,639
For you, it's simply...

265
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:22,240
it's...

266
00:10:22,240 --> 00:10:23,039
prepared just for you.

267
00:10:23,080 --> 00:10:23,320
Alright.

268
00:10:27,320 --> 00:10:28,159
Let's go, let's go.

269
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:28,960
Master,

270
00:10:29,039 --> 00:10:29,879
we want to go too.

271
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:30,720
Go where?

272
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:31,480
Stay home and read.

273
00:10:31,919 --> 00:10:32,519
Stay home and read.

274
00:10:32,559 --> 00:10:34,039
Master,

275
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:35,679
take the kids with you.

276
00:10:36,120 --> 00:10:36,720
I'll watch the house.

277
00:10:37,679 --> 00:10:38,039
Let's go.

278
00:10:38,879 --> 00:10:39,639
Come on, come on.

279
00:10:39,879 --> 00:10:40,639
Let's go, let's go.

280
00:10:40,960 --> 00:10:42,000
Hurry up, hurry up.

281
00:10:42,799 --> 00:10:43,559
Tiger Bone Wine—

282
00:10:44,200 --> 00:10:45,120
finally, we're saved.

283
00:10:47,440 --> 00:10:47,919
Lao Jiugui,

284
00:10:48,200 --> 00:10:49,200
we've been waiting for you!

285
00:10:49,679 --> 00:10:51,159
This is our shopkeeper's home.

286
00:10:51,960 --> 00:10:52,600
Please, come inside.

287
00:11:04,600 --> 00:11:05,240
This is it.

288
00:11:05,720 --> 00:11:06,080
Yeah.

289
00:11:10,440 --> 00:11:11,080
What are you giving

290
00:11:11,080 --> 00:11:11,879
this to me for?

291
00:11:12,279 --> 00:11:13,399
Shopkeeper Li said

292
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:15,000
to give me Tiger Bone Wine later.

293
00:11:17,559 --> 00:11:18,320
Where's your shopkeeper?

294
00:11:19,399 --> 00:11:20,120
He went to fetch the wine.

295
00:11:21,320 --> 00:11:22,360
He's scared, isn't he?

296
00:11:23,360 --> 00:11:24,320
Aren't you scared?

297
00:11:25,120 --> 00:11:25,720
Not scared.

298
00:11:27,720 --> 00:11:28,799
Then why is your lantern shaking?

299
00:11:29,399 --> 00:11:30,080
Just keeping up appearances.

300
00:11:30,799 --> 00:11:32,159
It's fine, scared is scared.

301
00:11:32,639 --> 00:11:33,480
Your shopkeeper

302
00:11:33,639 --> 00:11:34,759
dropped to his knees at our place.

303
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:37,320
I'm scared too.

304
00:11:40,440 --> 00:11:41,399
This residence,

305
00:11:41,600 --> 00:11:43,559
even if it's not an Auspicious Land,

306
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:45,279
it's perfectly proper.

307
00:11:47,000 --> 00:11:47,840
So tell me,

308
00:11:49,759 --> 00:11:51,039
what's been going on here?

309
00:11:52,120 --> 00:11:53,159
Every time it gets past midnight,

310
00:11:54,000 --> 00:11:55,000
we hear knocking at the door.

311
00:11:55,639 --> 00:11:56,639
But the moment we open it,

312
00:11:57,039 --> 00:11:58,080
there's not a soul in sight.

313
00:11:58,840 --> 00:11:59,879
Could it be a prank?

314
00:12:00,879 --> 00:12:02,080
When my brother and I were kids,

315
00:12:02,080 --> 00:12:02,720
when we got mischievous,

316
00:12:02,720 --> 00:12:03,559
we used to do that too.

317
00:12:03,960 --> 00:12:04,840
The shopkeeper and I

318
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,000
thought the same thing at first.

319
00:12:06,679 --> 00:12:07,799
But once it got past midnight,

320
00:12:08,279 --> 00:12:08,480
well...

321
00:12:08,639 --> 00:12:09,440
it wasn't just knocking,

322
00:12:09,679 --> 00:12:10,120
there was also...

323
00:12:11,600 --> 00:12:12,080
Here we go.

324
00:12:34,360 --> 00:12:35,000
Go on, tell me more.

325
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:35,720
What else was there?

326
00:12:36,000 --> 00:12:36,480
There was also...

327
00:12:36,519 --> 00:12:37,440
a female ghost's

328
00:12:37,919 --> 00:12:38,720
crying.

329
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:39,799
Here it comes.

330
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:46,360
You two wait here.

331
00:12:46,360 --> 00:12:47,080
Cowards.
